    <stitle>Side Mount Cooling Package - RE Bus - DESCRIPTION - Surge Tank</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Surge Tank</title>
        <figure id="f1202338" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg12/G1202338.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 2. Surge Tank</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. SURGE TANK</callout1>
                <callout1>2. CAP</callout1>
                <callout1>3. SITE GLASS</callout1>
                <callout1>4. AIR CLEANER HOUSING</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <para>The surge tank prevents over/under filling and accurate coolant level inspections. The surge tank
            efficiently collects air bubbles in the engine and radiator coolant to promote longer water pump and
            cylinder liner life. The coolant level can easily be checked by viewing the sight glass located on the side
            of the surge tank.
        </para>
        <para>The surge tank is located to the left side of the engine, faces the road side of the bus, and is mounted
            above the air cleaner housing. The surge tank can be accessed through the left-side rear compartment service
            door.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
